headline: URI Q4 Deep Dive: Large Project Growth Offset by Margin Pressures and Mixed Demand
summary: Equipment rental company United Rentals (NYSE:URI) fell short of the markets revenue expectations in Q4 CY2025 as sales rose 2.8% year on year to $4.21 billion. On the other hand, the company’s outlook for the full year was close to analysts’ estimates with revenue guided to $17.05 billion at the midpoint. Its non-GAAP profit of $11.09 per share was 6.1% below analysts’ consensus estimates.

headline: Why Herc (HRI) Shares Are Plunging Today
summary: Shares of equipment rental company Herc Holdings (NYSE:HRI) fell 7.3% in the afternoon session after a disappointing earnings report from its competitor, United Rentals (URI). Because URI missed Wall Street’s expectations for both revenue and profit, investors were concerned that these headwinds signal a broader slowdown across the entire equipment rental industry.
